 <div class="on-this-page">
<span class="right">
                    
                </span><p>Wednesday, September 5 - 0745hrs</p>        
            
                        
            
            
            
            <p>
<p>A TfL spokesperson said:<br>"We are pleased that the RMT has suspended its strike action at Metronet, following the clarification of all jobs and pensions issues.</p>
<p>"We will now work to provide the best possible Tube service on Wednesday. However, as the strike was suspended so late this evening, it will take time for us to restore a full service on all Underground lines today.&nbsp; </p>
<p>"Passengers should check before they travel to see how Tube services are running. Our staff will be available to provide travel advice and assistance on Wednesday."</p>
<p>The latest service update on all lines can be found at&nbsp;<a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/tfl/livetravelnews/realtime/tube/default.html">live travel news</a>.</p>
<p>Passengers can check before travelling via the following options:</p>
<ul class="linklist">
<li>The <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/">TfL website</a>; </li>
<li>The London Travel Info 24hrs telephone helpline: 020 7222 1234; </li>
<li>BBC Ceefax, page 436, or ITV's Teletext, page 164; and&nbsp; </li>
<li>Information on posters at stations and information boards at Tube stations.</li></ul>

     

        
        
        
